s Applying to Quarantine and Isolation  Visit the Specific Laws and Regulations Governing the Control of Communicable Diseases page.  Guidance for Importation of Human Remains into the United States for Interment  Visit the Guidance for Importation of Human Remains into the United States for Interment or Subsequent Cremation page.            Page last reviewed: February 24, 2020  Content source: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention , National Center for Emerging and Zoonotic Infectious Diseases (NCEZID) , Division of Global Migration and Quarantine (DGMQ)           home Quarantine and Isolation     About Quarantine and Isolation plus icon   History of Quarantine     Quarantine Stations plus icon   U.S. Quarantine Stations   Contact List, Map, Fact Sheets plus icon   Anchorage Quarantine Station  Atlanta Quarantine Station  Chicago Quarantine Station  Detroit Quarantine Station  El Paso & San Diego Quarantine Stations  El Paso & San Diego Quarantine Stations (en Espanol)   Honolulu Quarantine Station plus icon   Honolulu Jurisdiction Map    Houston Quarantine Station  Los Angeles Quarantine Station  Miami Quarantine Station  Minneapolis-St. Paul Quarantine Station  New York Quarantine Station  Newark Quarantine Station  Philadelphia Quarantine Station  San Francisco Quarantine Station  San Juan Quarantine Station  Seattle Quarantine Station  Washington D.C. Quarantine Station  Jurisdictions and Counties: California and Texas       Legal Authorities plus icon   Interim Final Rule: Control of Communicable Diseases: Foreign Quarantine; Suspension of Introduction of Persons Into United States From Designated Foreign Countries or Places for Public Health Purposes  FRN: Federal Travel Restrictions for Public Health Purposes  Specific Laws and Regulations  Final Rules for Control of Communicable Diseases: Interstate and Foreign – Scope and Definitions   Final Rule for Control of Communicable Diseases: Interstate and Foreign plus icon   Regulatory Burden Report  Q & As