ble balance and this starts with plant diversity to encourage insects, bees, small mammals, and birds.”   By Harriet Barber  TODAY’S MOODBOARD  Three pleasant things to put into your head  1.  An aesthetically pleasing performance in a Chinese city                The traditional Iron Flower performance which has taken place in Shandong, China.   Credit : Top Photo Corporation / Alarmy Live News      2.  Some scenic, sped-up  satellite shots of the sun         3.          Do you have some good news to share? What's made you happier in the past 24 hours? Have you seen a pleasing picture? Please send it all our way, either by commenting below or emailing coronapositive@telegraph.co.uk         Related Topics    Scotland,    Remembrance Sunday,    Coronavirus Positive                                                        The Telegraph values your comments but kindly requests all posts are on topic, constructive and respectful. Please review our commenting policy .     You need to be a subscriber to join the conversation. Find out more here .   Log In  Subscribe      Show comments               Advertisement     More stories          Related Topics    Scotland,    Remembrance Sunday,    Coronavirus Positive                                                              More from News               Live  Politics latest news: Quarantine list to be published imminently, Transport Secretary confirms         By  Cat Neilan     3 Jul 2020, 1:59pm                        Calls to teach Countryside Code in schools as lockdown brings rise in vandalism         By  Emma Gatten     3 Jul 2020, 1:55pm                          Live  Travel news: 60 countries exempt from UK quarantine to be announced today         By  Greg Dickinson     3 Jul 2020, 1:48pm                        Universities banned from bad mouthing rivals and tempting students with 'conditional unconditional' offers         By  Camilla Turner     3 Jul 2020, 1:39pm                     Why David Frost as National Security Adviser risks repeating mistakes made ahead of Iraq war         By  Dominic Nicholls     3 Jul 2020, 1:27pm                     Pilot of Australian seaplane lost control due to fumes, investigators of deadly 2017 crash find         By  Giovanni Torre     3 Jul 2020, 1:20pm                    More from The Telegraph               News website of the year                 Coronavirus        News        Politics        Sport        Business        Money        Opinion        Tech        Life        Style        Travel        Culture                     Subscribe now  Free for one month         Log in             See all News          UK news           UK news home        Scotland        Wales        Northern Ireland          World news           World news home        USA        Europe        Middle East        Asia        Australasia        Africa        Latin America          Royals           Royals home        The Queen        Prince Philip        Prince Charles        Duchess of Cornwall        Prince William        Duchess of Cambridge        Prince Harry        Duchess of Sussex        More...          Health        Defence        Science        Education        Investigations           Investigations home        Signals Network        Contact us          Global Health Security           Global Health Security home        Climate & People        Science & Disease        Terror & Security        Women & Girls        Opinion & Analysis                          Back to top        Follow us on:                                                            Contact us    About us    Rewards    Archive    Reader Prints    Branded Content    Syndication and Commissioning    Guidelines    Privacy    Terms and Conditions    Advertising Terms    Fantasy Sport    UK Voucher Codes    Betting Offers    Modern Slavery    © Telegraph Media Group Limited 2020               We've noticed you're adblocking.  We rely on advertising to help fund our award-winning journalism.  We urge yo